1) Temporary change on a worker node

First pick a worker:

oc get nodes

Open a debug shell on the worker:

oc debug node/<worker-node-name>
chroot /host

Examples inside the host:

hostnamectl
lsblk
systemctl status kubelet
cat /etc/containers/registries.conf
touch /root/test-file

Exit when done:

exit
exit

That is fine for inspection or one-off troubleshooting, but changes made this way are not the right long-term method for RHCOS nodes. Use MachineConfig for persistent node changes.

2) Temporary change on a master node

Same idea, but be extra careful:

oc debug node/<master-node-name>
chroot /host

Examples:

hostnamectl
systemctl status kubelet
crictl ps
journalctl -u kubelet -n 50

Do not make ad-hoc permanent edits on masters. Control plane nodes should be changed through supported APIs such as MachineConfig or other operator-managed objects.

3) Persistent change on worker nodes with MachineConfig

Example: create a file on all workers.

cat <<'EOF' > 99-worker-custom-file.yaml
apiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1
kind: MachineConfig
metadata:
  name: 99-worker-custom-file
  labels:
    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: worker
spec:
  config:
    ignition:
      version: 3.4.0
    storage:
      files:
      - path: /etc/myworker-note
        mode: 0644
        overwrite: true
        contents:
          source: data:text/plain;charset=utf-8;base64,V29ya2VyIG5vZGUgY3VzdG9tIGZpbGUK
EOF

oc apply -f 99-worker-custom-file.yaml

Check rollout:

oc get machineconfigpool worker
oc get machineconfig | grep worker-custom-file

Verify on a worker:

oc debug node/<worker-node-name>
chroot /host
cat /etc/myworker-note

MachineConfig is the standard supported path for OS-level node configuration.

4) Persistent change on master nodes with MachineConfig

Same thing, but target the master pool:

cat <<'EOF' > 99-master-custom-file.yaml
apiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1
kind: MachineConfig
metadata:
  name: 99-master-custom-file
  labels:
    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role: master
spec:
  config:
    ignition:
      version: 3.4.0
    storage:
      files:
      - path: /etc/mymaster-note
        mode: 0644
        overwrite: true
        contents:
          source: data:text/plain;charset=utf-8;base64,TWFzdGVyIG5vZGUgY3VzdG9tIGZpbGUK
EOF

oc apply -f 99-master-custom-file.yaml

Check rollout:

oc get machineconfigpool master
oc describe mcp master

Verify:

oc debug node/<master-node-name>
chroot /host
cat /etc/mymaster-note
5) Operator-style change: modify kubelet settings on workers

For kubelet-related settings, use the supported API instead of editing files by hand. OpenShift documents node customization through KubeletConfig as part of machine configuration.

Example: set maxPods for workers.

cat <<'EOF' > worker-kubeletconfig.yaml
apiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1
kind: KubeletConfig
metadata:
  name: set-max-pods
spec:
  machineConfigPoolSelector:
    matchLabels:
      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: ""
  kubeletConfig:
    maxPods: 250
EOF

oc apply -f worker-kubeletconfig.yaml

Check:

oc get kubeletconfig
oc get mcp worker
6) Operator-style change: modify CRI-O/container runtime on workers

For container runtime settings, use ContainerRuntimeConfig, which is also part of supported machine configuration workflows.

Example:

cat <<'EOF' > worker-crio.yaml
apiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1
kind: ContainerRuntimeConfig
metadata:
  name: worker-crio-config
spec:
  machineConfigPoolSelector:
    matchLabels:
      pools.operator.machineconfiguration.openshift.io/worker: ""
  containerRuntimeConfig:
    logLevel: debug
EOF

oc apply -f worker-crio.yaml

Check:

oc get containerruntimeconfig
oc get mcp worker
7) Useful rollback commands

Delete the change:

oc delete -f 99-worker-custom-file.yaml
oc delete -f 99-master-custom-file.yaml
oc delete -f worker-kubeletconfig.yaml
oc delete -f worker-crio.yaml

Watch pools return to updated state:

oc get mcp
watch oc get mcp
Best practice summary
Need to inspect a node now:
oc debug node/<node> && chroot /host
Need to persist OS/file/systemd/kernel-style changes:
MachineConfig
Need kubelet/runtime tuning:
KubeletConfig / ContainerRuntimeConfig
Avoid manual SSH edits as the normal method, especially on masters. Supported config should flow through the MCO / operator APIs.
